---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="LSCSS Comparisons"
    description="Comparing Layered Semantic CSS with other CSS methodologies."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Comparisons</p>

        <h1>
            Methodology comparisons
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            Most CSS methodologies try to solve the same problems: scale,
            maintainability, predictability, and developer sanity. They simply
            choose different trade-offs.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Quick reference
        </h2>

        <table class="comparison-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Methodology</th>
                    <th>Main focus</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>

            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>OOCSS</td>
                    <td>reuse</td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td>SMACSS</td>
                    <td>categorisation</td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td>BEM</td>
                    <td>naming clarity</td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td>ITCSS</td>
                    <td>specificity and layering</td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td>CUBE</td>
                    <td>modern practical architecture</td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td>LSCSS</td>
                    <td>layers, semantics, readability, maintainability</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Start with these debates
        </h2>

        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    BEM vs LSCSS
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Naming conventions versus semantic architecture. Useful for
                    teams carrying heavy legacy CSS.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    CUBE vs LSCSS
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Two modern approaches with different opinions on naming,
                    composition, and selector structure.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="hub-card">
                <h3>
                    @scope vs LSCSS
                </h3>

                <p>
                    Platform-native scoping versus architectural methodology.
                    These are partners, not rivals.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>
            Future comparison guides
        </h2>

        <ul>
            <li>Utility-first CSS versus semantic CSS architecture</li>
            <li>CSS Modules versus platform-native CSS</li>
            <li>Framework scoping versus cascade layers</li>
            <li>Tailwind versus LSCSS for long-term teams</li>
            <li>Component libraries versus design token systems</li>
            <li>When not to use LSCSS</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</DocsLayout>
